values: Just a couple pics(the ones on my work computer) from the first three (of 7) legs of our trip last year LONDON PARIS MERCALO

I am preparing for what will most likely be the greatest experience of my life.
In 29 days I will embark on a journey that I never thought possible-seven weeks in Europe with the love of my life...I have never been so excited about anything in my life and every day it gets closer, the more impatient I get.  I may never come back.
On July 5th at 9:35p.m. we leave on a non-stop BA flight to London were we will spend five days.  From there we will a short flight to Paris were we will spend five days and take side trips to Normandy and Versailles.  Then we will take a night train from Paris to Milan and spend a week with Jim's family and our friends Lorenzo and Daniella (who we met last summer) In the small town of Mercalo, a small town in Northern Italy between Como and Milan.  After a relaxing week and more food and wine than we will be able to handle, we will spend two nights in the senic Cinque Terre in the town of Vernazza where I will celebrate my 21st birthday.  Then we will spend four days in Rome seeing all the beautiful historical sights I've ever wanted to see.  From Rome we will go to Vienna where we will spend two nights and then it is on to Muich, Germany and drink in many a beer hall, then to Amsterdam (for the sights AND the coffe shops) and then will spend a relaxing to weeks in the beautiful city of Bergen, Norway.
This trip is a dream come true.

...AND FOR THOSE W/OUT A LIVEJOURNAL, i'LL ADD A PUBLIC ENTRY EVERY ONCE IN A WHILE, MAYBE
Nothing like curling up on the couch with my pink slippers, a blanket, a cup of hot chocolate and a quality CSI repeat...yea I feel better now.

I've always told myself never to regret any of my choices, that everything happens for a reason and life will eventually unfold the way its supposed to, but there are things that I can't help regretting right now. I dropped out of college last year before the first semester even ended- granted I was bloody miserable- but I still feel like an ass for doing it. I know I was wasting money and I didn't even know what I wanted to do, but who does that? My only conselation is that I've had alot of time to find myself and realize what I want to do with myself, well I figured out what I want to do with my life, but I still haven't "found myself". If it's even possible I think I've lost myself. I feel like I know myself even less than I did before and that's just plain frightening. I'm lost. So many things are running through my head all the time that I can't even keep my thoughts straight. And there is a certain someone that I can't get off my mind even though they shouldn't be in my thoughts at all. Hell, I don't even know who I am anymore. "I'm so cool, too bad I'm a loser. I'm so smart, too bad I can't get anything figured out. I'm so sane, it's driving me crazy. Anyone perfect must be lying. Anything easy has its cost."-barenaked ladies

Wow, what an AWESOME time! Band Camp 04 was the best so far! There were 21 counselors: Me, Nikki, Stacey, KateWatt, Foye, Megan Donnoly, Megan Shnelle, KateMcLean, Christine Dizuba, KaitMac, Elana DeFonte, Ski, Myles, JoeMac, Mark Lessard, Mark O'Connor, BJ, Matt Giblin, Colin Chambers, TM and Dave Hunter and we all got along great (with the exception of a couple incidences) and it was such a great week, especially the last night when we all satyed in the buffer cabin and 11 of us stayed up ALL NIGHT it was AWESOME! SKi shotguned 3 cans of coke and started tweekin out and he had us laughing hysterically for hours. We were all jacked up on soda and candy. We went up to the main lodge at 3 am to try and find more soda, we were unsuccesful, but we did steal milk and chocolate syrup and we took chocolate shots and ate the entire bottle in under 10 minutes. On the way back to the buffer cabin I busted my ass- I fell and twisted my ankle and cut my knee but it was funny cuz we were all messed up. It was like we were stoned and drunk, but we hadnt smoked or drank it was out of control and I got to know some great people. Last night Ski had us all over so we could get drunk for real. I had an awesome time, even though some people were doin some CRAZY shit that I didnt see commin. TM drove me home around 1:30 and I'd passed out by 3 and didnt wake up til 6 tonight! To summerize the whole week it was an awesome time with incredible people and I can't wait to go back next year 51 WEEKS TIL BAND CAMP!

So yesterday Nikki and I went to see M.Night Shyamalan's "The Village". It was one of the worst movies I've ever seen, If I were to see Mr. Shyamalan on the street, I would slap him across the face and DEMAND my $6.25 back(had it not been a matinee, rather than slapping him I'd kick him in the nuts) Nikki and I went expecting to see a scary movie. The review even had the audacity to say this movie would "Haunt your dreams", this couldnt have been further from the truth. Now I know many people are saying this movie is "brilliant", but the movie was a crock of shit, plain ans simple. I'll tell u how it ends so you don't waste your money. It ends up this professor was pissed off at the world and decided to do an experiment, moving a couple dozen families into a village surrounded by woods and beyond the woods, blocked by high fences, is civilization. He and the "elders" then claim the woods are haunted by "large creatures" and you cannot trespass or they'll kill you. They made costumes of these creatures and scare the shit out of people to keep them from leaving, thus living in a secluded village with no electricity, money, or medicine. wtf is that? I'm still pissed off. I got my mom to buy me 2 pairs of jeans and 4 shirts today horray! 10 days till band camp!!!

Life has been strange lately. I've been thinking about Tim alot lately which is BAD, very very BAD. He just had such a major impact on my life I dont think I could ever forget about him. I went Dashboard CRAZY after the concert- I ordered so much shit off the website I got another t-shirt, a sweatshirt, a poster and a CD and it all came yesterday so I'm a pretty happy camper. I havent stopped listening to them in like, weeks. I'm addicted. I am a Dashboard Confessional ADDICT. "Hello my name is Leah and I'm a dashboardaholic." "HI LEAH!! lol yea its that bad. I'm drinking coffee I'm gonna be up forever.

So I went to see Incubus @the Worcester Centrum Saturday night and it was, to say the least, AMAZING! Gina and I got up so close, Brandon Boyd was literally singing 20ft. in front of me! They sang a bunch of my favorites from Just a Phase to 11 am, it was UNBELIEVABLE!!! The drive home however, was a different story all together. We had just lit a fat blunt no more the five minutes ago when we got pulled over by a state cop. To cut the story short I had to get out of the squish the beautiful blunt all over the ground and he let us go with a speeding ticket for going 70 in a 60, we were SO lucky. But now I'm going to a party so I'll see y'all lata!

So after work tonight Nikki & I went to see the "Notebook" which I will admit, make me cry a bit, and made me remember how upset I am and how badly I want to be in love. I look around and everyone I see is in love and I hate to say it, but I'm so jealous. I want to be in love so badly, its like my goal in life- my ultimate dream- to have this beautiful storybook romance, even though I know it will never happen. And to top it all off, I woke up Tuesday to my cell phone ringing and how was it? None other than Tim Wheaton. "WHAT THE FUCK?!?" is what you would be thinking to yourself if you know me/knew me in high school. Tim Wheaton was my first love. It's like someone is playing this ridiculously evil practical joke on me. "I'm starting to fashion an idea in my head where I would impress you with every single word I said. Would come out insightful or brave or smooth or charming and you'd want to call me And I would be there every time you'd need me I'd be there every time... But for now I'll look so longingly waiting... For you to want me, for you to need me, for you to notice me" - d.c.

Last night (and by last night I mean Sunday night)Nikki and Foye stayed over my house. It was the first time in quite a while that I had a "Sleep Over" lol it makes me sound like I'm in junior high, but we had quite a few laughs. I'm really glad I've been hanging out with Foye and B-Riley lately, I've really missed them alot. I have been re-kindling some old friendships lately. Tonight for instince I got to hang out with Ryan and Pat for a little while, which was very cool.
I had alumni choir tonight, Nikki came for the first time which was excited. I felt like we were back in Madrigal class in high school, it was funny.
I'm enjoying this 3 day weekend from work far too much to take back Sunday nights. They FINALLY fired that terrible girl that never showed up for work. The fired her like two minutes after she punched in on Saturday night. I was about to leave and she came back to the front desk, punched out and left. It was very humerous. 
Thats all I got.

So Nikki woke my sorry ass up at 10am, and it was a good thing she did- we got alot accomplished today. We made tacos. Then we went to the Braintree mall and I got a new pair of shelltoes bringing my total to 4 pairs...I need more. Then we went to the Walpole mall and she got her ears double pierced and I got a red sox t-shirt. I had to work, but only til 8 and then Nikki, Foye and Bryan came to the Comedy show( at my work) with me. There was one guy there(I forget his name) who was absolutely hilarious. He's had Comedy Central and HBO specials. He's from Boston(Roslindale as a matter of fact) so he came to perform for fun. I almost died laughing. Then we went to Friendly's.
Overall today was a good day but strangely, I find myself depressed(again) for no reason. I dunno man, I just don't know I think I'm going crazy. this shit sucks.

I saw Shrek2 Monday night with Gina. We smoked a blunt and went to the last showing at like 10:30, it was a good time.
Last night I had Alumni choir which went very well. We are singing the most beautiful song, Sing Me To Heaven. Concert Chorale sang it my sophmore year, it's my favorite piece from high school. All the selections Moen chose for this year's alumni choir are great, I'm looking forward to learning them all.
Today I had a very nice lunch at Perk's with Katey Foye before work. Work wasn't terrible tonight, it wasn't good, but I didn't hate it. 
Thats about it for now.

There are alot of things that have been pissing me off lately and pushing me towards a depressed state but I don't wanna talk about those things, I'll talk about whats going well...
Ummm...
o yea thats right, I got NOTHING.

"This world is full, So full of crashing bores, And I must be one, cuz no one ever turns to me to say 'Take me in your arms, Take me in your arms, And love me'" - Morrissey
This is the best song lyric I've heard in quite some time. I can relate to this song quite alot at this point in my life.
So I have three days off in a row now, I don't know what I'm going to do with myself. I know I need the money, but I'm also very happy I dont have to deal with all those shitty people for 1/2 the week. Almost everyone at my work sucks. All the customers suck too. My job makes me angry, I'm always angry at work but up until now, I transformed that anger into really fake sweetness and I was always super nice to all the customers but lately, I'm just PISSED. Like today I sat a party of four at a table because the waitress next in order only had tables left. I got them they're settings and had gone back up to the front desk and two minutes later they came back up to the front desk and said "yea, we'd prefer a booth.." If your gonna be an asshole and ask for a booth, at least have the decency to ask BEFORE I seat you. People are such asses, you wouldn't believe. What's the big deal? Sit your ass at the fucking table and DEAL with it. Then this wicked shitty party of three came in like an hour later and I brought them to a table, they asked for a booth so I brought them to a booth, then 2 minutes later they moved back to the table... are you FUCKING KIDDING ME?!?!? People are shitty I hate everyone.
Ok I'm done with my rant, I needed to get that out, I feel much better now.
On the plus side, They let me go at 3 o'clock today and I was scheduled til 4:30. when my manager told me I could leave I was so excited- I'd never been cut early on a Saturday before.
